<TITLE> Ali Kabir returns as secretary </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 18 (bdnews24.com)--A S M Ali Kabir, a secretary to the government who went on LPR on Aug 22 last year, reported for duty at the establishment ministry on Thursday as a freedom fighter officer, a qualification that makes him eligible for an extended service life, an official said. Kabir was appointed establishment secretary early last year immediately after Sheikh Hasina took over as prime minister and then served as communications secretary before "retiring" on reaching 57 years of age. The government, meanwhile, decided to increase the retirement age of freedom fighter civil servants to 59. Back in service, Kabir, a 1979 BCS recruit, is now one of the most senior civil servants in Bangladesh and will be a strong contender to become the cabinet secret
